ubuntu-kernel-tests (0.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add standard version and changelog
  * remove .pyc files from git management
  * kernel-test-runner: remove the xfstests until we straighten out the drive issue
  * Merge branch 'master' of zinc.canonical.com:/srv/kernel.ubuntu.com/git/ubuntu/kernel-testing
  * pre-testing-setup: additional package 'attr' needed for xfs testing
  * Make metrics filenames more unique
  * Add ability to pass in lists of tests
  * remove parameters to process_metrics, no longer needed
  * job-autotest: chown the results tree to $USER.$USER instead of jenkins.jenkins
  * job-autotest: chown the results tree to $USER.$USER instead of jenkins.jenkins
  * job-autotest: Put each jobs results/default in it's own directory tree on the jenkins server
  * kernel-tests-runner: Added the stress test to the mix
  * job-autotest: Added code back in to copy the results tree over to the artifacts directory on the jenkins server.
  * job-autotest: Added check for KERNEL_TEAM_JOB
  * Added a timestamp to the attributes and generate a 'test-attributes.json' file as well as print to stdout.
  * kernel-tests-runner: enable the xfstests tests
  * pre-testing-setup: create the xfstests user
  * kernel-tests-runner: enable the correct tests
  * Handle control.ubuntu tests and xfstests pre-testing requirements
  * kernel-tests-runner: call out to gather the additional information we are interested in
  * gather*: code to print out data about the host on which the test was run
  * job-autotest: tar up the results directory tree so there is something to look at when the wheels come off
  * A set of scripts for use with QA regression testing.

